Rating: 3
I adapted this recipe for one bunch of collards. Used as much bacon as seemed doable for two people, one small onion, 1/2 cup chicken broth, 1T cider vinegar, 1/2T brown sugar. Poured out some of the bacon fat to cook onions. It's hard for me to watch greens go from bright to brownish, and can't imagine cooking them for an hour. Instead I simmered the collards with lid on for maybe 10 minutes, added the onion in, turned up the heat and stirred until the broth had almost completely evaporated, added the bacon back in. It was pretty durn delish.

