Rating: 4
This recipe is so unbelievably good. I have made this a few times and tried out a few variations: 1. Red wine vinegar instead of cider vinegar (I actually prefer this variation, but I'm sure any kind of vinegar will work perfectly well) 2. Reducing the amount of brown sugar (I *do not* recommend this if this is your first time making the recipe: the brown sugar seems to have a tenderizing effect on the collard greens, and when omitted, the coarser stems and ribs are much tougher -- not to mention, the sugar is a great compliment to the acidity of the vinegar) 3. Doubling the chicken broth, vinegar, and pepper flakes with a pinch of extra brown sugar (The more potlikka the better! This does give the collards a slightly more 'stewed' texture, but if you're serving with cornbread you'll want a little more liquid than this recipe will produce) 4. Brown onions when I didn't have the red ones (no significant difference, so no need to make a run to the store if you've already got regular onions in your pantry) But all that said, the recipe as written is fantastic.

Rating: 4
This is delicious. I would recommend reducing the sugar, especially if there's added sugar in your vinegar. Otherwise the sugar dominates. Personally, I used only 1/3 of the sugar called for here. On another note: 8 servings is extremely optimistic; 1/8 of this recipe is really just a taste. I once ate half a recipe of this as an entree size portion (for 1 person). Count on serving four generously or six sparingly with this recipe.

