I made half the recipe with only a couple of adjustments, finding the instructions useful for someone relatively new to Southern cooking. I would advise a more generous hand with the red chili flakes, though it is easy enough to use hot sauce at the table. I eliminated the brown sugar and instead added 1/2 cup of unfiltered apple cider while also increasing the amount of chicken stock. The extra liquid was not only welcome "pot likker", it seemed necessary even in a heavy enameled cast iron pot. I ended up increasing cooking time, too, though not to the point of dissolving the leaves into a silken dew. If you like truly flavorful dishes, I might amp up the vinegar, too, though just by a little.

